Agent: For the **2025/2026 tax year** (1 March 2025 ΓÇô 28 February 2026), SARS 
confirms that the **personal income tax brackets remain unchanged** from the 
prior year. [1][2][7]

The **individual (and special trust) tax table** for this period is: [1][2]

1. **R1 ΓÇô R237 100**  
   18% of taxable income  

2. **R237 101 ΓÇô R370 500**  
   R42 678 + 26% of taxable income above R237 100  

3. **R370 501 ΓÇô R512 800**  
   R77 362 + 31% of taxable income above R370 500  

4. **R512 801 ΓÇô R673 000**  
   R121 475 + 36% of taxable income above R512 800  

5. **R673 001 ΓÇô R857 900**  
   R179 147 + 39% of taxable income above R673 000  

6. **R857 901 ΓÇô R1 817 000**  
   R251 258 + 41% of taxable income above R857 900  

7. **R1 817 001 and above**  
   R644 489 + 45% of taxable income above R1 817 000  

These brackets are taken directly from the **SARS Budget tax guide for 
2025/26** and the SARS ΓÇ£Rates of Tax for IndividualsΓÇ¥ / ΓÇ£Income TaxΓÇ¥ pages, 
which state that there were **no changes to the personal income tax brackets** 
for the 2026 year of assessment (i.e. the 2025/2026 tax year). [1][2][4][7]

