User: What are the current individual income tax brackets in South Africa for 
the 2025/2026 tax year?

Agent: For the 2025/2026 South African tax year (1 March 2025 ΓÇô 28 February 
2026), SARS confirms that the personal income tax brackets for individuals 
remain unchanged from the prior year. [1][2][4][8]

According to the SARS ΓÇ£Rates of Tax for IndividualsΓÇ¥ table (2026 tax year) and 
the SARS Budget Tax Guide for 2025/26, the brackets for **individuals and 
special trusts** are: [1][8]

**2026 year of assessment (1 March 2025 ΓÇô 28 February 2026)**  

- **R1 ΓÇô R237 100**  
  18% of taxable income  

- **R237 101 ΓÇô R370 500**  
  R42 678 + 26% of taxable income above R237 100  

- **R370 501 ΓÇô R512 800**  
  R77 362 + 31% of taxable income above R370 500  

- **R512 801 ΓÇô R673 000**  
  R121 475 + 36% of taxable income above R512 800  

- **R673 001 ΓÇô R857 900**  
  R179 147 + 39% of taxable income above R673 000  

- **R857 901 ΓÇô R1 817 000**  
  R251 258 + 41% of taxable income above R857 900  

- **R1 817 001 and above**  
  R644 489 + 45% of taxable income above R1 817 000  

SARS explicitly states that for the **2026 year of assessment (1 March 2025 ΓÇô 
28 February 2026)** there were **ΓÇ£no changesΓÇ¥** to the personal income tax 
brackets compared with the immediately preceding year. [1][3][4][8]

